            <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:#15803d;margin-bottom:0.25rem;">ADA & WCAG AA Compliant — Built Into Every Site</h3>
            <p style="color:#166534;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.6;">All websites I build follow WCAG AA accessibility guidelines — the standard required under the Americans with Disabilities Act. This means your site works for everyone, including users with visual, motor or cognitive disabilities. Accessible websites also rank better in Google. This site scores a perfect <strong style="color:#15803d;">400/400 on Google Lighthouse</strong> and a perfect <strong style="color:#15803d;">10/10 on the WAVE accessibility checker</strong> across every single page — that's the bar I hold all my work to.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;">
